        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 8:39AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 838 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of Gilchrist, or 20 miles east of Beach City, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Gilchrist, Rollover Pass, High Island, Stowell, Winnie, Bolivar
Peninsula, and Oak Island.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
